result.name: Tin Hau Temple, Tai Shu Ha

reviews.text: An historical temple which has served the local area for many generations. At the temple there is a very very old Banyan tree that people also paid respect to up until recently when a fence was put around it to protect it's roots. The main deity within the grounds is "天后娘娘" (Tin Hau Leong Leong). There is a great feeling of spirituality and peace here. It's definitely a place worth visiting.
It's nice
One of the oldest Tin Hau Temples in the terrotory
Very famous temple In Yuen Long.

A nice historical Chinese temple with many sections to pray. There is a rare hundred year old tree.  When it is Chinese New year you can book a POON CHOI for 10 to 12 people, which the test is good and the price is just right. There is a big parking lot if you drive there. If only for visiting I think you will take about 2 hours max to visit and 1 hour more if you eat there.

result.name: 大樹下天后古廟

reviews.text: 很有特色，得有名氣的古廟。
多謝今年初朱鑑徽師父幫忙解簽,雖然等咗好耐，真的在4月5日前回來了!而且决定結婚!其實當時在天后廟搵過幾位師父,林姑娘解話唔會返來同作福,有位林X玲居士不停叫我作福買金牌,另外-一個李X芝師傅不停要我批命,解簽是照字讀既,咩春天唔會有消息-全程都是叫我批命,佢價格批埋都要二仟二佰元.點都好-真的多謝朱師父！
領教過林X玲女居士，簽文都讀錯，求其講兩句叫我作福，跟住嚇我會有流血之災又催我買金牌保平安，發現流流地走頭轉去李X芝睇睇，呢個仲勁照字讀書然後問我出生日期，嘩！佢手指郁郁，原來更流，問答遊戲，不停chok你講嘢！不停推銷批命，跟著又係作福，千祈咪上當！其他枱冇人既，最後在大樹下牆邊有寫生肖的文章，寫我啲嘢好準，可惜唔記得咩名，有冇人可以話我知！
